                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        Scribe: 
                           ʾAbuna Walda Mikāʾel.  ʾAbuna
                        Walda Mikāʾel is mentioned as the scribe in the supplication formula on
                           <locus target="#53va">53va</locus>.<date>19th century (?).</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>Abbreviations used throughout Text III:</item>
                           <item>መድ(ኀ)፡ ዓ(ለ)፡ for መድኀኔ፡ ዓለም፡</item>
                           <item>መድ፡ ዓ፡ ክ፡ for መድኀኔ፡ ዓለም፡ ክርስቶስ፡</item>
                           <item>መድ፡ ዓ(ለ)፡ ክር(ስ)፡ for መድኀኔ፡ ዓለም፡ ክርስቶስ፡</item>
                           <item>ሰላ፡ for ሰላም፡</item>
                           <item>ስብሐ፡ for ስብሐት፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; several groups of lines on the incipit
                           page of Text I, alternating with black lines; two lines in the incipit of
                           Text II and III; incipit of each section in Text II; every second letter
                           in some words in Text II (e.g., fols. 11rb, 32vb); the first word of each
                           strophe in Text III; the words salām “salutation” and sǝbḥat “glory” in
                           Text III; elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">It is possible that another hand was
                        involved in the writing on <locus target="#76ra">76ra</locus>.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">- <locus target="#3r">3r</locus> (incipit
                        page of Text I): coloured (yellow, blue, outlined in black) ornamental band;
                        crosses, intersecting lines.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#35r">Fol. 35r: </locus>
                        <desc>the Virgin and Child.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#35v">Fol. 35v: </locus>
                        <desc>Crucifixion.</desc>The miniature is protected with a textile
                        curtain.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1"> <locus target="#76ra">f. 76ra</locus>
                           <desc>-b: Donation note. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"> <locus target="#76ra">76ra-</locus>b: ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡
                              ዘተሣየጠቶ፡ በንዋያ፡ ቅድስት፡ ወህሪት፡ ወለተ፡ መድኅን፡ ወወ[ሀ]በቶ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ደንዴራ፡ ከመ፡
                              ይኩኖ፡ መድኃኒተ፡ ነፍስ፡ ወሥጋ፡ ለአቡሃ፡ ወለእማ፡ ገብረ፡ ዮሐ[ን]ስ፡ ወለተ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ወለደቂቃ፡ ወለተ፡
                              አቢየ፡ እግዚእ፡ ወለተ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፋሐቃ፡ ወዘተአገላ፡ በስልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡
                              ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in brilliant vermillion ink and states that
                              Walatta Madḫǝn purchased the book and donated it to the church of
                              Mikāʾel Dändera. The note also mentions her father Gabra Yoḥannǝs, her
                              mother Walatta Gabrǝʾel, and her daughters Walatta ʾAbiyä ʾƎgziʾ and
                              Walatta Takla Hāymānot. The note concludes with a condemnation for
                              those who stole the book. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title መደሃን የአለም is written on the front cover with
                           white paint.
 - Tamallas-sign, in the shape of a cross (+) indicating
                           the place where the omissions, written in the left margin, belong: <locus target="#11va">11va</locus>.
 - Omitted letters or words inserted
                           interlineally in the main hand: e.g., <locus target="#4vb">4vb</locus>,
                           6va, 22va, 43ra, 48ra, 55vb.
 - Omitted letter inserted in blue pen
                           in a secondary hand: <locus target="#5rb">5rb</locus>.
 - Erasures:
                              <locus target="#20ra">20ra</locus>, 26vb, 33rb.
 - Erasure marked
                           with thin red lines: <locus target="#44rb">44rb</locus>.
 - Immediate
                           corrections indicated by thin black lines or series of dashes above and
                           below the word(s): e.g., <locus target="#4vb">4vb</locus>, 5va, 10ra,
                           22rb, 32vb, 46vb, 50rb, 58vb.
 - Space for rubrication left unfilled:
                              <locus target="#48va">48va</locus>.
 - Unfilled line marked with
                           thin red lines: <locus target="#17rb">17rb</locus>.
 - Notes in
                           pencil on <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>, 76v.
 - Several names are
                           written in the supplication formulas in a secondary hand (possibly the
                           same as Additio 1) in brilliant vermillion ink: Gabra ʾIyasus (e.g.,
                              <locus target="#7rb">7rb</locus>, 11rb, 25rb, 36va, 57va), Walatta
                           Madḫǝn (e.g., <locus target="#11rb">11rb</locus>, 19ra, 30vb, 46vb, 57va,
                           70va), ʾabuna Kidāna Māryām (e.g., <locus target="#10vb">10vb</locus>,
                           22ra, 32ra, 50rb, 62vb, 70va), Walatta ʾAbiyä ʾƎgziʾ (e.g., <locus target="#10vb">10vb</locus>, 22ra, 28vb, 53va, 62vb, 70va), Gabra
                           Yoḥannǝs (<locus target="#70va">70va</locus>), Walatta Gabrǝʾel (<locus target="#70va">70va</locus>). The name of Tasfā Ḥǝywat is crudely
                           written in red pencil in the supplication formulas e.g., on <locus target="#7rb">7rb</locus>, 11rb, 15ra, 44va, 56va, 66ra, 76ra.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Readings are indicated by the names of the days of
                              the week written in frames in the upper margin, in a secondary hand:
                              ዘሰኑይ፡ <locus target="#10vb">fol. 10vb</locus> ዘሠሉስ፡ <locus target="#19ra">fol. 19ra</locus> ዘረቡዕ፡ <locus target="#25rb">fol.
                                 25rb</locus> ዘሐሙስ፡ <locus target="#30vb">fol. 30vb</locus> ዘዓርብ፡
                                 <locus target="#38ra">fol. 38ra</locus> ዘቀዳም፡ <locus target="#44va">fol. 44va</locus> ዘዕሁድ፡ <locus target="#50rb">fol. 50rb</locus>
                              ዘሰኑይ፡ <locus target="#52vb">fol. 52vb</locus> ዘሠሉስ፡ <locus target="#53va">fol. 53va</locus> ዘረቡዕ፡ <locus target="#54va">fol.
                                 54va</locus> ዘሐሙስ፡ <locus target="#55ra">fol. 55ra</locus> ዘዓርብ፡
                                 <locus target="#55vb">fol. 55vb</locus> ዘቀዳም፡ <locus target="#56va">fol. 56va</locus> ዘዕሁድ፡ <locus target="#57va">fol.
                              57va</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
